    • Constructor Detail

      • SettingsModelEnumeration

        public SettingsModelEnumeration(java.lang.Class<T> enumType,
                                java.lang.String configName,
                                T defaultValue)
        Creates a new object holding an enumeration value. The current value will be set to the specified default value.
        Parameters:
        enumType - Enumeration class this setting is based on. Must not be null.
        configName - The identifier the value is stored with in the org.knime.core.node.NodeSettings object. Must not be null.
        defaultValue - The initial value. Must not be null.

      • setValueAsString

        public void setValueAsString(java.lang.String newValueAsString)
        Set the value stored to the new value represented as string. This string must match an enumeration name of the registered enumeration class. If not, the default value will be used instead and a warning will be logged.
        Parameters:
